(10 comments)

This is still based on top of an abandoned patch. You will need to rebase this so it is directly on master, and include the changes you had tried to make in the abandoned patch.

Easiest at this point is probably from the command line. Do something like the following:

git rebase -i HEAD~2
[squash the two commits into one]
[address comments to fix issues]
git add .
git commit --amend
[use this patch's commit message, including Change-Id line]
git review

That should combine the two commits into one and have it based on master.
